title: Area Volleyball: United falls to Wethersfield
text: Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 10:17 PM Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 10:17 PM KEWANEE â€” The United High School volleyball team suffered its first conference loss in a 13-25, 25-15, 25-20 loss to Wethersfield on Wednesday. The Red Storm (23-4, 8-1) were led by Joelle Shea with a match-best 14 kills. Emma Marshall had 14 digs, Lauren Sperry made four blocks and served two aces, Mallory Flynn gave out 16 assists and Claire Wynne added 15 assists for United. The Register-Mail
